{
  "title": "Spherical Harmonics",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "944685aabb6f3e2f",
      "text": "Spherical harmonics are the eigenfunctions of the Laplace operator on the 2-sphere. They form a basis and are useful and convenient to describe data on a sphere in a consistent way in spectral space. Spherical harmonic transforms (SHT) are the spherical counterpart of the Fourier transform, casting spatial data to the spectral domain and vice versa. They are commonly used in various pseudospectral direct numerical simulations in spherical geometry, for simulating the Sun or the liquid core of the Earth among others [Glatzmaier, 1984; Sakuraba, 1999; Christensen et al., 2001; Brun & Rempel, 2009; Wicht & Tilgner, 2010]."
